<TITLE> LG Elec to boost output from existing plasma line </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SEOUL, July 2 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) -- South Korea's LG Electronics Inc said on Sunday it would increase its plasma display panel (PDP) output by 22 percent starting July by boosting productivity at its biggest production line. LG, the world's second-biggest plasma display maker after Japan's Matsushita Electric Industrial Co Ltd, has been working to streamline its loss-making PDP operation by closing older facilities and raising efficiency. LG said in a statement its monthly capacity would rise to 440,000 units from 360,000 as it introduces a new glass-cutting process that produces eight plasma panels per glass substrate instead of the current six. In May LG said it was halting production at the smallest of its three PDP lines to save costs. Plasma screens, which once dominated the large flat-screen TV market, have lost ground to rival liquid crystal displays. But plasma makers are betting on stronger seasonal demand in the second half and focusing on larger screens for premium TV models. Matsushita plans to double its PDP output capacity in two years. Plasma panel demand is expected to rise to 4 million in the fourth quarter from 2.3 million in the first quarter, DisplaySearch forecast, according to L
